00:00:51.050 --> 00:00:54.080
By the way, everything I'm
doing now is called kinematics.

00:00:54.080 --> 00:00:57.309
In other words,
kinematics is a study of how to

00:00:57.309 --> 00:01:00.609
describe a system completely at
a given time.

00:01:00.609 --> 00:01:02.912
For example,
in classical mechanics for a

00:01:02.912 --> 00:01:06.310
single particle the complete
description of that particle is

00:01:06.310 --> 00:01:09.460
given by two things,
where is it,

00:01:09.460 --> 00:01:13.170
and what its momentum is.
 

00:01:13.170 --> 00:01:18.090
Dynamics is the question of how
this changes with time.

00:01:18.090 --> 00:01:21.007
If you knew all you could know
about the particle now can you

00:01:21.007 --> 00:01:22.030
predict the future?
 

00:01:22.030 --> 00:01:24.580
By predict the future we mean
can you tell me what x

00:01:24.580 --> 00:01:26.953
will be at a later time and
p will be at a later

00:01:26.953 --> 00:01:27.349
time.
 

00:01:27.349 --> 00:01:29.709
That's Newtonian mechanics.
 

00:01:29.709 --> 00:01:32.358
So the kinematics is just how
much do you need to know at a

00:01:32.358 --> 00:01:34.230
given time, just x and
p.

00:01:34.230 --> 00:01:36.840
Once you've got x and
p everything follows.

00:01:36.840 --> 00:01:39.300
As I mentioned to you,
the kinetic energy,

00:01:39.300 --> 00:01:41.388
for example,
which you write as

00:01:41.388 --> 00:01:45.039
½mv^(2),
is given just in terms of

00:01:45.039 --> 00:01:47.989
p,
or in higher dimensions the

00:01:47.989 --> 00:01:52.132
angular momentum is some cross
product of position and

00:01:52.132 --> 00:01:54.783
momentum,
so you can get everything of

00:01:54.783 --> 00:01:57.760
interest just by giving the
position and momentum.

00:01:57.760 --> 00:02:02.894
I claim now the equivalent of
this pair of numbers in this

00:02:02.894 --> 00:02:07.310
quantum world is one function,
ψ(x).

00:02:07.310 --> 00:02:09.941
So it's a lot more information
than you had in classical

00:02:09.941 --> 00:02:10.419
physics.
 

00:02:10.419 --> 00:02:12.367
In classical physics two
numbers tell you the whole

00:02:12.367 --> 00:02:12.680
story.
 

00:02:12.680 --> 00:02:15.218
Quantum theory says "give
me a whole function",

00:02:15.218 --> 00:02:17.890
and we all know a function is
really infinite amount of

00:02:17.890 --> 00:02:20.562
information because at every
point x the function has a

00:02:20.562 --> 00:02:22.840
height and you've got to give me
all that.

00:02:22.840 --> 00:02:25.729
Only then you have told me
everything.

00:02:25.729 --> 00:02:26.848
That's the definition.
 

00:02:26.848 --> 00:02:29.282
And the point is ψ
can be real,

00:02:29.282 --> 00:02:32.145
ψ can be complex,
and sometimes ψ

00:02:32.145 --> 00:02:33.220
is complex.
 

00:02:33.220 --> 00:02:35.670
So we can ask,
you've got this function,

00:02:35.670 --> 00:02:38.626
